                <h1>Citizens United: The Impact on Campaign Finance</h1>
                <p>Citizens United v. FEC is a landmark Supreme Court case that changed the landscape of campaign finance in the U.S. It ruled that political spending is a form of protected speech under the First Amendment, allowing corporations and unions to spend unlimited funds on elections, significantly impacting political influence and democracy.</p>
